fields.title: Don Quixote
fields.author: Miguel de Cervantes
fields.description: Don Quixote (1605, 1615) by Miguel de Cervantes is a seminal Spanish novel often cited as the first modern novel. It follows Alonso Quixano, a middle-aged nobleman who, maddened by chivalric romances, renames himself Don Quixote and sets out to revive knighthood. Along with his pragmatic squire, Sancho Panza, he battles imagined foes, blending satire, adventure, and existential philosophy

fields.title: The Wizard From Vahan
fields.author: Candy Ray
fields.description:
Jasper does a time-jump which is supposed to be a meditation, but it goes wrong, and he finds himself in a parallel world about to embark on a mission that he does not want.

Jasper is an apprentice magician in a society of the future, where chaos magic has become the dominant religion. He does a time-jump which is supposed to be a meditation, but it goes wrong, and he finds himself in a parallel world about to embark on a mission that he does not want.

fields.title: 13 Years in America
fields.author: Melanie Steele
fields.description:
The thought-provoking story of one woman's search for happiness and fulfilment in modern-day America.

The thought-provoking story of one woman's search for happiness and fulfilment in modern-day America.

After moving to the United States from Canada in 1998, a free-spirited young woman rejects the status quo and embarks on a journey to discover what it means to be truly happy and fulfilled in the Land of Opportunity

fields.title: Beasts of New York
fields.author: Jon Evans
fields.description:
A violent, epic, action-packed urban quest full of very eccentric, often hilarious, extremely dangerous characters who also happen to be animals.

Beasts of New York is a novel by award-winning author Jon Evans: a violent, epic, action-packed urban quest full of very eccentric, often hilarious, extremely dangerous characters who also happen to be animals -- the wildlife of New York City, to be exact.

fields.title: A New Spartan: Nikos Kokiniakos
fields.author: Charles Coiro
fields.description: A young Greek boy living in an isolated small village seeks to continue the Spartan way of living and tries to join the army at age 7, the same as the Spartans. His attempt to join is picked up by the newspapers and read by a wealthy Greek man from New York who offers to send him through Military School. Nikos becomes a courier of funds slated for helping the Conservative faction to overthrow the Liberals in Greece. His adventures awaken his understanding in his friendships with men and women.

fields.title: New Testament Commentary by a Mathematician
fields.author: Victor Porton
fields.description:
This is a New Testament commentary written by a mathematician, which contains many new revelations. Free ebook.

This is a New Testament commentary written by a mathematician, which contains many new revelations.
In Gospel there are things which are not revealed when just reading the text but only after a serious scrutinized study.

fields.title: The Flint Lord
fields.author: Richard Herley
fields.description: This novel of intrigue, violence and betrayal in the land of our Stone Age forefathers is a magnificent successor to the author's The Stone Arrow. Here, spurring the Flint Lord's drive for conquest, is his passion for his beautiful, decadent sister, a drive and a passion which lead inexorably to catastrophic consequences.

fields.title: Planning Armageddon
fields.author: George McNeur
fields.description:
When Josh and Tom's wives discover there are people 'out there' planning to ensure the 2012 Doomsday prophecies are fulfilled, they decide to take matters into their own hands and on their terms ...

What would it take to make you commit bio-terrorism on a global scale?

fields.title: Time Management for Mercenaries
fields.author: Dai Alanye
fields.description: How do Travel, Adventure and Good Pay sound to you? Can you handle a bow, a spear, perhaps a sword? Join a team of men and women to forever alter history--for better or worse. Come on! What's the worst that can happen? Sickness, death by misadventure, some mistake that drops you in the middle of nowhere, instant oblivion? Sure, but look on the bright side. Well... No, I can't actually describe the bright side--our project is confidential. But you do like adventure, don't you? And how's your attitude toward a bit of looting and pillaging?

fields.title: From Rome to Byzantium
fields.author: Tom Green
fields.description: This book provides a detailed overview of trading activity in the Roman and Byzantine Mediterranean, grounded in recent archaeological research. It is argued in what follows that while state-sponsored trading was undoubtedly important in both eras ...

fields.title: Introduction to Philosophy: Ethics
fields.author: George Matthews
fields.description: We often make judgments about good and bad, right and wrong. Philosophical ethics is the critical examination of these and other concepts central to how we evaluate our own and each others' behavior and choices. This text examines some of the main threads of discussion on these topics that have developed over the last couple of millenia, mostly within the Western cultural tradition.

fields.title: An Introduction to the Corps of Marine Trained Messiahnists!
fields.author: Mike Knowles
fields.description:
Looking for a religion based on science aimed at atheists? Like being shouted at by a former gunnery sergeant in the USMC? Computer Book.

Looking for a religion based on science aimed at atheists? Like being shouted at by a former gunnery sergeant in the USMC? Well, look no further! Your prayers have been answered. Created by a published writer with the aid of a former gunnery sergeant in the USMC, Messiahnism is a religion for the computer generation.

fields.title: COORG - A State of Mind
fields.author: Animesh Anand
fields.description:
This travelogue, painted in the backdrop of an unearthly part of the cosmos, is a reflection of eternal memories one experiences in such ethereal setup..

This travel book, painted in the backdrop of an unearthly part of the cosmos, is a reflection of eternal memories one experiences in such ethereal setup. These memories might not be confined to an individual; neither do they belong to a single group of friends who visited the valley. Instead, the memoir b

fields.title: Treasure Island
fields.author: by Robert Louis Stevenson
fields.description: Squire Trelawney, Doctor Livesey, and the rest of these gentlemen having asked me to write down the whole particulars about Treasure Island, from the beginning to the end, keeping nothing back but the bearings of the island, and that only because there is still treasure not yet lifted, I take up my pen in the year of grace 17‚Äî, and go back to the time when my father kept the "Admiral Benbow" Inn, and the brown old seaman, with the saber cut, first took up his lodging under our roof.

fields.title: Book Of Wisdom
fields.author: Advanced Society of Paranormal Studies (ASPS)
fields.description: This is a book for thinkers. People who like to explore mysterious truths about the universe, and writings about deep matters that affect us all, right here, right now. Subjects include: intelligence, knowledge, science, meta-physics, materialism, ancient wisdom, reincarnation, spirituality, ancient texts, paranormal phenomena, mind, yoga, life, death, natural phenomena, nature, consciousness, supernatural powers, physics, the universe, religion, and philosophy.

fields.title: The Mathematical Universe
fields.author: Manjunath.R
fields.description: We become more aware of how little we know about how the cosmos functions as we learn more about it. The Universe is full of secrets, from the doorstep of our own Solar System to the far-off shores of the intergalactic ocean. With the help of a large number of telescopes and satellites, we have increased our understanding of the universe. We have been investigating the history of the cosmos, from the Big Bang through comets' peculiarities and our curiosity about the chemistry of stars. One thing unites many of the most prevalent theories: they start from a mathematical framework that aims to explain more than our existing leading theories can.

fields.title: Anthology Of Poetry: Vol Two
fields.author: Catherine Lean
fields.description:
This is a collection of my poetry which I have written over a number of years. It covers many subjects and styles but Mostly rhyming.

This is a collection of my poetry which I have written over a number of years. It covers many subjects and styles but Mostly rhyming. My works are centred a lot around animals but there is something for everyone here. I hope you enjoy reading and find something useful to take away with you.

Writing to me is a great joy. Nature inspires me with her diverse richness, but I can also see that same beauty in objects, and in these pages you will see that you can write about anything if you give your mind free reign.

fields.title: Poetry Pieces of Europe, Vol. 1
fields.author: European Poetry Collective
fields.description:
This book is a result of joint activities of people all across Europe who engaged themselves in its preparation, according to their own field of specialization. Free ebook.

This is an English language anthology that represents the new European poetic scene through authors, whose mother tongue is not initially English. This book is a result of joint activities of people all across Europe who engaged themselves in its preparation, according to their own field of specialization. Authors, designers, proof-readers and editors, all having English as a second or even a third language, have been brought together, led by one common idea - to spread the variety of European cultures in a literature product, presented in an international linguistic tool.

fields.title: Poetry for Modern Children
fields.author: N.
fields.description:
Poetry for modern children is a book written for today's children who face challenges such as peer pressure, fad diets and so on.

Poetry for modern children is a book written for today's children who don't only face challenges such as peer pressure etc., but children who also come across stereotypes in our modern society and fad diets and so on.

To regain self esteem and be proud of who they are and where they come from has been my aim in writing. There are other playful poems that children at a more younger age can read.

fields.title: Aswito Darling
fields.author: Brian Kibet
fields.description:
Dear Aswito darling ... we love till we are tired of love! More wonderful poetry from Brian Kibet. Available for free download in PDF and ePub formats.

Be aware, these words are naked. Be aware, these simple words are not written in ordinary ink but in tears and the sound of laughter. Be aware, these words are written in the throes of passion and in the bottoms of despair, that sometimes words was all I had. These words are sad and happy and sometimes both in equal measures.

fields.title: Essays on Art and Literature
fields.author: John Xavier
fields.description:
These essays focus on illuminating their subjects in a profound way so that the reader will be inspired to engage in a philosophical reflection of said works on their own. Free PDF.

Discussing various historical works of culture, as well as the broader context of human creativity, these essays focus on illuminating their subjects in a profound way so that the reader will be inspired to engage in a philosophical reflection of said works on their own.

fields.title: Illuminating the Twilight
fields.author: Carol L Rizzolo, PhD
fields.description:
When those who lay dying tell their stories and speak their truths, those of us at the bedside are called to pay attention and to listen with our hearts.

This work is freely given and has particular value for those travelling through the end of life.

A scan of four thousand years of extant literature reveals that the emotional experiences of dying individuals has always been and continues to be the poetic expression of the human body itself. This project showcases the wisdom literature found in the collective voices of our human ancestors.

fields.title: The Wild Goose
fields.author: Mori Ogai
fields.description:
The events of my story took place some time ago, the thirteenth year of the Meiji era, to be exact. I remember because at that time I was living in a boardinghouse called the Kamijo.

A recreation of Tokyo in the 1880s by one of Japan‚Äôs most influential novelists.

Mori ≈ågai (1862‚Äì1922), one of the giants of modern Japanese literature, wrote The Wild Goose at the turn of the century. Set in the early 1880s, it was, for contemporary readers, a nostalgic return to a time when the nation was embarking on an era of dramatic change. ≈ågai‚Äôs narrator is a middle-aged man reminiscing about an unconsummated affair, dating to his student days, between his classmate and a young woman kept by a moneylender. At a time when writers tended to depict modern, alienated male intellectuals, the characters of The Wild Goose are diverse, including not only students preparing for a privileged intellectual life and members of the plebeian classes who provide services to them, but also a pair of highly developed female characters.

fields.title: Pride and Prejudice
fields.author: Jane Austen
fields.description:
The novel follows the character development of Elizabeth Bennet, the dynamic protagonist of the book who learns about the repercussions of hasty judgments.

Pride and Prejudice is a romantic novel of manners written by Jane Austen. Though this popular work of classic literature is known as a romance, it can also be considered a satirical book. The novel follows the character development of Elizabeth Bennet, the dynamic protagonist of the book who learns about the repercussions of hasty judgments and comes to appreciate the difference between superficial goodness and actual goodness.

fields.title: Tales of Murder, Mystery & Suspense Vol 1
fields.author: Will Lankstead
fields.description:
A Collection of eight short stories about Murder, Mystery and Suspense. free ebook.

A Collection of eight short stories about Murder, Mystery and Suspense. Such titles include: Small Talk, Little Jimmy Slater, Nice Work if you can get it!, Sara, the Underpass.

fields.title: Veil
fields.author: Reginald Cook
fields.description:
Thriller book: Bounty hunters on the trail of a vicious serial killer--wrestle a forty-year old conspiracy when Charlie Ivory, old and homeless, confronts them with a startling confession--He's a murderer.

This is Book One in the VEIL crime books series. Download Book Two, The Hammer of God.

Robert Veil and Nikki Thorne, bounty hunters on the trail of a vicious serial killer--wrestle a forty-year old conspiracy when Charlie Ivory, old and homeless, confronts them with a startling confession--He's a murderer.

fields.title: Inspector Zhang Gets His Wish
fields.author: Stephen Leather
fields.description:
Detective inspector Zhang of the Singapore Police Force is called to investigate the death of an American businessman in a hotel suite. Follow Zhang as he uses his skills of deduction to unravel the clues and solve the crime.

Detective inspector Zhang of the Singapore Police Force is called to investigate the death of an American businessman in a hotel suite. Follow Zhang as he uses his skills of deduction to unravel the clues and solve the crime. From the pen of Stephen Leather, one of the UKs best thriller books writers.

fields.title: 200 Steps Down
fields.author: Morris Kenyon
fields.description:
When his crime boss in Odessa, Ukraine, decides to up his game by getting involved in people trafficking, Nicolae Caramarin must make a choice. Should he turn a blind eye to the horrors he witnesses?

When his crime boss in Odessa, Ukraine, decides to up his game by getting involved in people trafficking, Nicolae Caramarin must make a choice. Should he turn a blind eye to the horrors he witnesses and carry on being a good soldier for the gang; or take his stand and bring them all down in the only way he knows how?

A fast-paced, tense and exciting crime/noir thriller. Contains scenes of a sexual nature, graphic violence, strong language and drug abuse. It is not intended for the easily offended or persons under eighteen years. You have been warned, so if you read on, don't blame me.

Short stories:
Bacharach's Bungalow
Lowriser Letdown

fields.title: Eclipsed: Selected Writings of Fiction and Non-Fiction
fields.author: Peter McMillan
fields.description:
11 pieces of short fiction and 13 works of non-fiction, addressing themes sufficiently dystopian to get us to pay attention to some of the possible futures of our species.

A brief collection of writings that blends 11 pieces of short fiction and 13 works of non-fiction. This volume is essentially a continuation of Writings Near the End of the Human Era, which addresses themes sufficiently dystopian to get us to pay attention to some of the possible futures of our species.

fields.title: Considering: Science Fiction for Idealistic Minds
fields.author: Deborah Loraine Kean
fields.description:
Enter the exciting worlds of Deborah Loraine Kean's science fiction and speculative fiction short stories. Free ebook.

Enter the exciting worlds of my science fiction and speculative fiction short stories.

Excerpt Bad Penny:

fields.title: Tensions Between Science and Spirituality with Philosophy and Logic as Referee
fields.author: Dickson Olabiyi Adelusi
fields.description:
A thought-provoking exploration where science and spirituality converge and diverge, revealing their intricate relationship in shaping human understanding

Dive into a thought-provoking exploration where science and spirituality converge and diverge, revealing their intricate relationship in shaping human understanding and existence. In "Tensions Between Science and Spirituality with Philosophy and Logic as Referee," the author navigates these realms with nuance and depth, inviting readers to ponder the profound implications of their coexistence. At its core, the book challenges the notion of science and spirituality as opposing forces, illustrating instead their complementary roles in our quest for truth and meaning.

fields.title: Settings and Atmosphere in Your Fiction
fields.author: Paula Puddephatt
fields.description:
Free book! Need tips on creating authentic fictional settings, particularly in realistic fiction? Or advice about how to build suspense and tension in your stories, and create a sense of atmosphere and mood?

Need tips on creating authentic fictional settings, particularly in realistic fiction? Or advice about how to build suspense and tension in your stories, and create a sense of atmosphere and mood? Ever heard of the term White Room Syndrome? In this short reference book, I discuss all of the above.
